resposta: The Eastern Front of World War I was a major theater of operations during the war  stretching from the Baltic Sea to the Black Sea. It involved many of the major European powers  including Germany  Russia  Austria-Hungary  and Great Britain  as well as several smaller nations. The front was marked by intense fighting and significant casualties  with key battles such as the Battle of Tannenberg  the Brusilov Offensive  and the Battle of the Somme. Ultimately  the Eastern Front played a crucial role in determining the outcome of World War I.
